Anticipated Questions
Q: Why not use openssl speed to reproduce this issue?
A: openssl speed uses randomized inputs and does not reliably exercise the specific (a, m) boundary conditions required to trigger this deterministic carry loss.

Q: Is this a CPU hardware erratum?
A: No. The ADX/BMI2 instructions themselves behave correctly. This is a software logic issue in how the parallel carry chains are merged in the assembly implementation.

Q: Does this affect all x86_64 CPUs with ADX?
A: In principle, yes. Any CPU executing the bn_mul_mont_adx path may be affected, depending on the execution timing and register interactions at the carry-merge point.

